<taxonomicName authority="Hood" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Dolichothrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolichothrips indicus" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indicus">Dolichothrips indicus (Hood)</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="83" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
Although described from India, this species has been found widely across the Pacific, including Japan, Taiwan, Guam, New Caledonia, and French Polynesia (
<bibRefCitation author="Mound, LA" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="11" pageNumber="90" pagination="79 - 96" title="Taxonomic Studies on Dolichothrips (Thysanoptera: Phlaeothripinae), pollinators of Macaranga trees in Southeast Asia (Euphorbiaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3956.1.4" volume="3956" year="2015">Mound and Okajima 2015</bibRefCitation>
). On Hawaii it has been found established on the leaves of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Macaranga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Macaranga tanarius" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tanarius">Macaranga tanarius</taxonomicName>
, but is not recorded from any of the other Hawaiian Islands. It was recorded in the &quot;Hawaiian all-species checklist database&quot; (
<bibRefCitation author="Bianchi, FA" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Hawaiian Entomological Society" pageId="10" pageNumber="89" title="Hawaiian All-Species Checklist Database" url="http://hbs.bishopmuseum.org/checklist/query.asp" year="2002">Bishop Museum 2002</bibRefCitation>
) under the synonymic name 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Dolichothrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolichothrips nesius" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nesius">Dolichothrips nesius</taxonomicName>
Stannard.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
